# File: tests/features/vault-distill.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-session-distillation-hook/requirements.md
# Issue: #11

Feature: Session distillation hook
  As a Claude Code + Obsidian user who ends many short sessions
  I want each finished session automatically distilled into a dated Markdown note in my vault
  So that my vault accumulates browseable memory without manual note-taking

  Background:
    Given a scratch HOME at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/home"
    And a scratch Obsidian vault at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/vault"
    And obsidian-memory is installed and setup against "$VAULT"
    And a stub "claude" CLI is on PATH returning a fixed distillation by default

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: A non-trivial session ends and is distilled
    Given a transcript at "$HOME/.claude/projects/my-proj/<sid>.jsonl" of size 5000 bytes
    And "distill.enabled" is true
    When SessionEnd fires with {transcript_path, cwd="/path/to/my-proj", session_id, reason="clear"}
    Then a new file exists under "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/my-proj/" matching "^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-\\d{6}\\.md$"
    And the file starts with "---" frontmatter
    And the frontmatter contains "project: my-proj", "end_reason: clear", "source: claude-code"
    And the body is the stub "claude" output
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" has a new link line immediately under "## Sessions"
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Edge Case ---

  Scenario: Trivial session is skipped
    Given a transcript of size 1500 bytes
    When SessionEnd fires with that transcript_path
    Then no file was created under "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/"
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" is unchanged
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Distillation returns empty — fallback stub written
    Given the stub "claude" CLI is configured to return an empty string
    And a valid 5000-byte transcript
    When SessionEnd fires
    Then the created note's body is the fallback stub
    And the body contains "Distillation returned no content. See transcript:"
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" still gained a link line
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Alternative Paths ---

  Scenario: Index.md does not exist yet
    Given "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" does not exist
    When a successful distillation runs
    Then "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" is created
    And it contains "# Claude Memory Index"
    And it contains "## Sessions"
    And it contains the new link line
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Index.md exists but has no "## Sessions" heading
    Given "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" exists with content "# My custom index\n\nSome user notes here.\n"
    When a successful distillation runs
    Then "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" still contains "# My custom index" and "Some user notes here."
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" ends with a "## Sessions" section containing the new link line
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Distillation disabled via config
    Given "distill.enabled" is false in the config
    When SessionEnd fires with a valid transcript
    Then no note file was created
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" was not modified
    And the stub "claude" CLI was not invoked
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Error Handling — silent ---

  Scenario: Missing claude CLI
    Given "claude" is unavailable on the hook subshell PATH
    When SessionEnd fires
    Then no file writes occur
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Missing jq dependency
    Given "jq" is unavailable on the hook subshell PATH
    When SessionEnd fires
    Then no file writes occur
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Missing config file
    Given "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" does not exist
    When SessionEnd fires
    Then no file writes occur
    And the hook exit code is 0

  Scenario: Unreadable transcript path
    Given the SessionEnd payload references "/nonexistent/path.jsonl"
    When the hook fires
    Then no note file is created
    And the hook exit code is 0

  # --- Security ---

  Scenario: Project slug sanitization prevents path escape
    Given the session "cwd" is "/some/path/My Weird & Project/../etc"
    When the hook derives the slug
    Then the slug matches "^[a-z0-9-]+$"
    And the slug does not contain ".." or "/"
    And any resulting write is strictly under "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/"

  Scenario: Nested claude CLI receives CLAUDECODE cleared
    Given the parent Claude Code process exported "CLAUDECODE=1"
    And the stub "claude" is configured in "env_echo" mode so it echoes "$CLAUDECODE"
    When SessionEnd fires with a valid 5000-byte transcript
    Then the stub's captured "CLAUDECODE" value is an empty string
    And the child did not abort with "Cannot be launched inside another Claude Code session"

  # --- Performance / Edge ---

  Scenario: Large transcript is capped at 200 KB
    Given a transcript whose extracted conversation would exceed 200 KB
    When SessionEnd fires
    Then the prompt piped to "claude -p" is <= 204800 bytes
    And the hook completes successfully
    And a note file is created

  Scenario: Mixed content-array and content-string messages
    Given a transcript JSONL with some messages having "content" as an array of parts and others as a plain string
    And the array parts include "text", "tool_use", and "tool_result" types
    When the hook extracts the conversation
    Then both content shapes are flattened to newline-joined text
    And "tool_use" parts render as "[tool_use: <name>]"
    And "tool_result" parts render as stringified content
    And the resulting note is created successfully
